The U.K. Government tomorrow willrelease the first of its Retail Price Index (RPI) figurescalculated on a revised group of components and rebased onJanuary 1987, as previously announced, the EmploymentDepartment said.    The index, Britain's measure of inflation, is for February.Earlier data will not be revised as there are no equivalentfigures including the new components, a spokesman said.    Previously, the RPI base was January, 1974.    Market forecasts centre on a 0.4-0.5 pct monthly rise inFebruary and a year on year rate about 4.0 pct. The governmentforecasts annual inflation will be 4.0 pct at the end of 1987. REUTER&#3;